.TH man 1 "03 March 2021" "0.9" "_printf man page"
.SH NAME
.B _printf man page
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B Use: _printf [format] [argument] ...

.B Prototype:
int _printf(const char * format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf() is a family of functions that produces output according to a format

.SH OPTIONS

.B %c
- Prints a single character

.B %s
- Prints a string of characters

.B %i
- Prints an integer

.B %d
- Prints a decimal

.B %%
- Prints a single %

.SH IN FUTURE DEVELOPMENT (NOT SURE)
.B %b
- Converts from decimal to binary

.B %u
- Prints an unsigned integer

.B %x
- Converts a decimal to hexadecimal (in lowercase letter characters when applicable)

.B %X
- Converts a decimal to hexadecimal (in uppercase letter characters when applicable)

.B %o
- Converts a decimal to octal

.B %r
- Reverses a string

.B %R
- Converts to ROT13

.B %S
- Prints non-printable characters in hexadecimal

.SH EXAMPLES
.B --- Print a single character 'a' followed by a newline:

_printf ("%c\\n", 'a');

# a


.B --- Print a string of characters 'Holberton School!' followed by a newline:

_printf ("%s\\n", "Holberton School!");

# Holberton School!


.B --- Print an integer number 3 followed by a newline:

_printf("%i\\n", 3);

# 3


.B --- Print a single % followed by a newline:

_printf("%%\\n")

# %

.B More examples in the future (or maybe not)

.SH SEE ALSO
man page printf(3) (man 3 printf)

.SH BUGS
Not Sure ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

